#command git status

git status [<options>] [<file>...]

The 'git status' command is used in Git to display the current state of your directory and its relation to the Git repository.

<options>
-s: Provides a shorter, more compact output format.
-b: Displays additional information about the branch status.
-u: Specifies how untracked file are displayed.
-v: Displays more detailed information.
-uno: Hides untracked files from the status output.

git status
git status -s
git status -u all
git status -b
